# Pagination

A IDS pagination is a component for switching between multiple pages of data in a table or a long list.

This is used primarily in our other IDS components, such as `DataGrid`, and `Table`.

## Installation & Import

```bash
yarn add @ids-ts/pagination
```

```tsx
import { Pagination } from '@ids-ts/pagination';
```

## Props API

| Prop | Type | Required | Description |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| `totalPages` | `number` | Yes | - |
| `totalItems` | `number` | Yes | total number of items |
| `pageSize` | `number` | Yes | Number of items/rows to show per page |
| `activePage` | `number` | Yes | the current active page number |
| `isLoadingTotals` | `boolean` | No | when true, shows loading state instead of total pages count and total items |
| `loadingComponent` | `JSX.Element` | No | - |
| `allowNextWhenLoading` | `boolean` | No | when true, allows the next button to remain enabled when in loading mode (isLoadingTotals === true) |
| `showBoundaryControls` | `boolean` | No | when true, shows the first and last buttons |
| `preventPageJump` | `boolean` | No | when true, prevents the ability to jump to a specific page |
| `labels` | `{ page?: string; of?: string; items?: string }` | No | Labels for i18n (e.g., `'Page'`, `'of'`, `'items'`). |
| `fullSummaryContent` | `string` | No | - |
| `of` | `string` | No | label for the 'of' word, ex: Page 1 of 5 or 1-50 of 600 items |
| `summaryItems` | `string` | No | label applied to summary section as kind of data, ex: 1 of 5 items |
| `previousPageButtonAriaLabel` | `string` | No | aria label applied to the previous page button |
| `nextPageButtonAriaLabel` | `string` | No | aria label applied to the next page button |
| `goToPageButtonAriaLabel` | `string` | No | aria label applied to each page button, ex: Go to page 2, where the number 2 will be automatically assign |
| `pageNumberTextFieldAriaLabel` | `string` | No | aria label applied to the page number text field |
| `goToFirstPageButtonAriaLabel` | `string` | No | aria label applied to the 'Go to first page' button |
| `goToLastPageButtonAriaLabel` | `string` | No | aria label applied to the 'Go to last page' button |
| `onPageChange` | `(selectedPage: number) => void` | Yes | - |

<details>
<summary>Full TypeScript Interface</summary>

```typescript
export interface PaginationProps extends ThemeableElement<'div'> {
  /** total number of pages of data available. you should calculate this
   * number based on the total number of rows of data and the page size */
  totalPages: number;
  /** total number of items */
  totalItems: number;
  /** Number of items/rows to show per page */
  pageSize: number;
  /** the current active page number */
  activePage: number;
  /** when true, shows loading state instead of total pages count and total items */
  isLoadingTotals?: boolean;
  /**
   * Specify the loading component to render when isLoadingTotals === true
   * When not specified, will render pagination data no matter the value of isLoadingTotals
   */
  loadingComponent?: JSX.Element;
  /** when true, allows the next button to remain enabled when in loading mode (isLoadingTotals === true) */
  allowNextWhenLoading?: boolean;
  /** when true, shows the first and last buttons */
  showBoundaryControls?: boolean;
  /** when true, prevents the ability to jump to a specific page */
  preventPageJump?: boolean;
  /** Labels for i18n related to pagination */
  labels?: {
    /** label for the 'Page' word, ex: Page 1 of 5   */
    page?: string;
    /** pass the full summary content,
     * this assumes all calculations are done by
     * consumer so that this content to make sense. */
    fullSummaryContent?: string;
    /** label for the 'of' word, ex: Page 1 of 5  or  1-50 of 600 items */
    of?: string;
    /** label applied to summary section as kind of data, ex: 1 of 5 items */
    summaryItems?: string;
    /** aria label applied to the previous page button */
    previousPageButtonAriaLabel?: string;
    /** aria label applied to the next page button */
    nextPageButtonAriaLabel?: string;
    /** aria label applied to each page button, ex: Go to page 2, where the number 2 will be automatically assign */
    goToPageButtonAriaLabel?: string;
    /** aria label applied to the page number text field */
    pageNumberTextFieldAriaLabel?: string;
    /** aria label applied to the 'Go to first page' button */
    goToFirstPageButtonAriaLabel?: string;
    /** aria label applied to the 'Go to last page' button */
    goToLastPageButtonAriaLabel?: string;
  };
  /** onPageChange callback to be use when changing page via Previous, Next buttons or
   * when changing page via the page number text field. This function will be called
   * with the new page number as the first argument. Consuming teams should use this
   * to update the activePage prop in this pagination object. */
  onPageChange: (selectedPage: number) => void;
}
```

</details>

